cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with content-based image retrieval using convolutional neural networks and deep hashing models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on large-scale data and the training of deep hashing models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on two datasets, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia) as well. Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm to preserve semantic hierarchy structures, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
